        "timestamp": 1740896741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It seems <code>attribute [local reducible]</code> worked in Lean 3 from <a href=\"https://github.com/search?q=repo%3Aleanprover-community%2Fmathlib4%20local%20reducible&amp;type=code\">search results</a> but no longer works after porting. I think it could potentially remove an <code>erw</code> in one of my proofs due to <code>AdjoinRoot</code> not being reducible. Is there anything available in Lean 4 that achieves the same effect?</p>",
        "id": 530304734,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1753264239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/270676-lean4/topic/.60unfold.60.20needed.20before.20.60rfl.60/near/530304734\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It seems <code>attribute [local reducible]</code> worked in Lean 3 from <a href=\"https://github.com/search?q=repo%3Aleanprover-community%2Fmathlib4%20local%20reducible&amp;type=code\">search results</a> but no longer works after porting. I think it could potentially remove an <code>erw</code> in one of my proofs due to <code>AdjoinRoot</code> not being reducible. Is there anything available in Lean 4 that achieves the same effect?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Does <code>unseal foo in...</code> work for you here? This is syntax for <code>attribute [local semireducible] foo</code></p>",
        "id": 530310582,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Henson",
        "timestamp": 1753266154
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Lean says</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"kn\">local</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">semireducible</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`AdjoinRoot</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">currently</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">semireducible</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">irreducible</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expected</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Note</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">allowUnsafeReducibility</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">override</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">reducibility</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">status</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">validation</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>If I add <code>set_option allowUnsafeReducibility true</code>, I still can't remove the <code>erw</code>. I think I need to turn the semireducible def <code>AdjoinRoot</code> into a reducible one.</p>",
        "id": 530377328,
